https://prez.dev/description.@value: A categorization of disciplines or topics that the broad field of Earth science can be subdivided into, i.e. a listing of the Fields of Research, or subjects, to which a geoscience dataset, publication, observation/activity, or entity pertains. The vocabulary also contains relevant disciplines that intersect with the various Earth science fields, such as biological sciences and built environment and design, as well as entries related to collection and heritage management. Notations included are those from the 2020 ANZSRC listing (see History Note) or in common use in the geoscience community.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: The part of cultural heritage that deals with items that have no physical existence, such as past and current traditions or living expressions inherited from our ancestors and passed on to our descendants (e.g. oral traditions, performing arts, social practices, rituals, festive events), knowledge and practices concerning nature and the universe, or the knowledge and skills to produce traditional crafts.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#hist.@value: Adapted from the Fields of Research vocabulary from the Australian and New Zealand Standard Research Classification (ANZSRC, 2020). Definition adapted from UNESCO.
